6.Replace a character.
Strings in Python are immutable, which means you cannot change individual characters in a string.

s="Ayushi"
new=""
for ch in s:
    if ch=='u':
        new+='o'
    else:
        new+=ch
print(new)
o/p-->Ayoshi
Instead of doing only 5 operations, Python actually copies
1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5=15
tc=O(n²)
sc=O(n)



2nd approach-->
s = s.replace('u', 'o')
print(s)
